Target bearing 020.

3
00:01:20,027 --> 00:01:22,114
Contact 020.

4
00:01:22,280 --> 00:01:25,700
- Range 20,000.
- Range 20,000 yards.

5
00:01:25,867 --> 00:01:29,705
- Course 255.
- Course 255 true.

6
00:01:29,871 --> 00:01:33,291
- Speed 13.
- Speed 13 knots.

7
00:01:33,458 --> 00:01:35,127
Cowboys.

8
00:02:39,733 --> 00:02:42,027
"Enchanter, Mobile."

9
00:02:44,488 --> 00:02:48,367
Well, we're a long way from home.
Wake 'em up!

10
00:02:58,043 --> 00:02:59,711
It's the Navy!

11
00:03:00,837 --> 00:03:02,673
Quick, put out the flag!

12
00:03:13,684 --> 00:03:14,851
Enchanter!

13
00:03:15,018 --> 00:03:18,063
This is the United States
Coast Guard.

14
00:03:18,230 --> 00:03:21,650
Heave to
and prepare to be boarded.

15
00:03:35,038 --> 00:03:39,501
Enchanter, you are a US-flag ship,
and we are going to board you.

16
00:03:39,668 --> 00:03:42,129
Heave to now.

17
00:03:53,306 --> 00:03:56,810
Muster your crew on the bow.

18
00:04:12,534 --> 00:04:14,661
You two, go forward.

19
00:04:15,996 --> 00:04:18,332
Randall, come with me.

20
00:04:23,253 --> 00:04:27,090
- Stay where you are.
- Kneel down.

21
00:04:30,135 --> 00:04:33,555
Captain. Captain?

22
00:04:34,431 --> 00:04:36,350
Go ahead, Senior Chief.

23
00:04:36,516 --> 00:04:42,230
It's a bad one. I think you'd better
send over the video camera.

24
00:04:59,665 --> 00:05:01,792
Jack, come on in.

25
00:05:04,586 --> 00:05:07,923
- How high is the pile on your desk?
- About this high.

26
00:05:08,090 --> 00:05:10,467
- Now it's this high.
- What have you got?

27
00:05:10,634 --> 00:05:15,639
You heard about that business in the
South Caribbean? I need the details.

28
00:05:15,806 --> 00:05:19,518
- By when?
- As soon as you can.

29
00:05:19,685 --> 00:05:23,230
- OK.
- Jack? Be discreet.

30
00:05:24,898 --> 00:05:28,819
- What do you mean?
- You'll find out.

31
00:05:30,570 --> 00:05:32,656
Mysterious...

32
00:05:35,075 --> 00:05:37,119
I love a mystery.

33
00:05:41,206 --> 00:05:44,710
- Ryan, John P.
- Let him through.

34
00:05:46,712 --> 00:05:49,506
- Here you go.
- Thank you.

35
00:05:49,673 --> 00:05:53,010
- You know where you're going?
- Yes. Thank you.

36
00:05:53,760 --> 00:05:57,014
- Where do I park?
- Right over there.

37
00:06:08,316 --> 00:06:10,819
Main passageway, going forward.

38
00:06:10,986 --> 00:06:13,697
Master stateroom,
blood on the deck...

39
00:06:13,864 --> 00:06:17,659
19 cartridges were recovered,

40
00:06:17,826 --> 00:06:23,373
as well as the two weapons
that fired them.

41
00:06:23,540 --> 00:06:30,339
Blood samples taken were
consistent with the crew, Hardin

42
00:06:30,505 --> 00:06:34,468
and his wife
and his son and daughter.

43
00:06:35,886 --> 00:06:38,555
I got blood on the sheets and pillow

44
00:06:38,722 --> 00:06:41,224
on both starboard and portside racks.

45
00:06:41,391 --> 00:06:43,393
There's blood there, too.

46
00:06:43,560 --> 00:06:48,231
They were killed in their staterooms
apparently as they slept.

47
00:06:48,398 --> 00:06:51,360
Dragged topside
and thrown overboard.

48
00:06:52,736 --> 00:06:57,407
The two men in custody surrendered
after a brief attempt to escape.

49
00:06:57,574 --> 00:07:01,286
What do we know about them?
The men in custody?

50
00:07:03,372 --> 00:07:07,459
Half a dozen arrests for drug
trafficking in Bogota, Mr President.

51
00:07:08,543 --> 00:07:10,045
Drugs.

52
00:07:11,963 --> 00:07:15,467
Suspected ties to the Cali cartel,
not Medellin...

53
00:07:15,634 --> 00:07:19,137
- You alright, James?
...according to DEA.

54
00:07:19,304 --> 00:07:22,015
- Why?
- Nothing exotic, sir.

55
00:07:22,182 --> 00:07:25,727
Straight piracy and murder.
It's not the first time.

56
00:07:27,562 --> 00:07:31,024
It's the first time
it was a friend of mine.

57
00:07:32,567 --> 00:07:34,736
Yes, sir.

58
00:07:41,076 --> 00:07:44,496
- What was that? You alright?
- Yeah.

59
00:07:44,663 --> 00:07:47,457
I haven't slept in 36 hours.
Did I make any sense?

60
00:07:47,624 --> 00:07:50,377
What did you say?
Just kidding. Good job.

61
00:07:54,673 --> 00:08:00,012
- You should give diplomacy lessons.
- To call it as I see it is myjob.

62
00:08:00,178 --> 00:08:03,140
- And he's yours.
- Wait for me.

63
00:08:07,686 --> 00:08:09,771
Shut the door.

64
00:08:13,066 --> 00:08:18,113
I promised the American people I'd
do something about the drug problem.

65
00:08:18,280 --> 00:08:20,407
You are.

66
00:08:20,574 --> 00:08:24,578
You support the Colombians' efforts
against the cartels...

67
00:08:24,745 --> 00:08:30,375
And accomplish nothing. Do these
drug dealers think we're powerless?

68
00:08:30,542 --> 00:08:36,465
That they can keep doing this kind of
thing, and there's no response ever?

69
00:08:37,632 --> 00:08:41,386
Are you suggesting
a course of action, sir?

70
00:08:41,553 --> 00:08:47,434
The course of action I'd suggest is
a course of action I can't suggest.

71
00:09:01,782 --> 00:09:05,535
I'm... not sure
where that leaves us.

72
00:09:09,373 --> 00:09:13,251
These drug cartels represent
a clear and present danger

73
00:09:13,418 --> 00:09:17,255
to the national security
of the United States.

74
00:10:07,180 --> 00:10:09,891
Do you know what you've done?

75
00:10:10,058 --> 00:10:11,893
I killed a thief,

76
00:10:12,519 --> 00:10:14,396
a thief who was stealing...

77
00:10:16,898 --> 00:10:18,358
...from me!

78
00:10:19,526 --> 00:10:22,529
And his wife, and his son,
and his daughter,

79
00:10:22,696 --> 00:10:25,240
apparently with no thought
of the consequences.

80
00:10:28,327 --> 00:10:33,623
Should I let his children avenge their
father's death when I least expect it?

81
00:10:34,374 --> 00:10:36,126
He was a good friend

82
00:10:36,293 --> 00:10:39,880
and a political ally
of the President of the United States.

83
00:10:48,597 --> 00:10:50,807
That doesn't surprise me.

84
00:10:51,683 --> 00:10:55,062
- It should concern you.
- What can they do?

85
00:10:55,228 --> 00:10:58,482
Come after me? Arrest me?

86
00:10:58,648 --> 00:11:01,026
You're scaring me.

87
00:11:02,444 --> 00:11:07,240
Will you stop long enough for me
to tell you something important?

88
00:11:09,785 --> 00:11:11,703
Thank you.

89
00:11:14,498 --> 00:11:20,921
Listen. You pay me to counsel you,
and I am counselling you.

90
00:11:21,088 --> 00:11:24,841
I'm keeping you alive
with information.

91
00:11:25,008 --> 00:11:27,386
If you disregard my counsel

92
00:11:27,552 --> 00:11:30,931
and keep running your business
the way you have been,

93
00:11:31,098 --> 00:11:35,769
with your balls and not your head,
two things will happen.

94
00:11:35,936 --> 00:11:39,564
I'll quit, and you'll get killed.

95
00:11:50,784 --> 00:11:54,830
You forgot to tell me
about your scouting trip.

96
00:11:54,997 --> 00:11:59,251
- No, I didn't.
- You made another contact. Who?

97
00:11:59,418 --> 00:12:02,629
Castro always asked me
about my sources.

98
00:12:02,796 --> 00:12:08,427
- I always gave him the same answer.
- Castro didn't pay you what I pay.

99
00:12:08,593 --> 00:12:11,722
This one will cost you nothing.

100
00:12:13,432 --> 00:12:15,225
Awoman.

101
00:12:15,392 --> 00:12:18,020
You're using a woman.

102
00:12:24,901 --> 00:12:27,029
It won't float.

103
00:12:28,697 --> 00:12:31,825
- John, what do you want? Toast?
- Waffles!

104
00:12:31,992 --> 00:12:35,537
- No time for waffles.
- Anybody seen my keys?

105
00:12:35,704 --> 00:12:38,582
Either on the front hall table
or in your pocket.

106
00:12:38,749 --> 00:12:41,543
- Where aremykeys?
- Pancakes!

107
00:12:41,710 --> 00:12:44,046
- Toast, please.
- Thank you.

108
00:12:44,212 --> 00:12:45,380
Bye, Dad.

109
00:12:45,547 --> 00:12:48,675
- Bye, pal.
- It won't float!

110
00:12:48,842 --> 00:12:53,096
It's not supposed to float, it's
a submarine. It goes under water.

111
00:12:53,263 --> 00:12:54,931
Jack.

112
00:12:57,267 --> 00:12:59,394
Hello?

113
00:13:01,480 --> 00:13:02,856
When?

114
00:13:05,400 --> 00:13:07,736
I thought I had the flu.

115
00:13:07,903 --> 00:13:11,907
I'd still think so if they weren't
telling me otherwise.

116
00:13:13,492 --> 00:13:16,328
What are they telling you?

117
00:13:17,245 --> 00:13:23,335
Pancreatic cancer of an aggressive
nature, if I heard them right.

118
00:13:23,502 --> 00:13:26,713
Well, what does it mean?

119
00:13:27,589 --> 00:13:30,550
I guess it means I'm in big trouble.

120
00:13:30,717 --> 00:13:35,347
- I mean, can they operate, or?
- Maybe.

121
00:13:35,514 --> 00:13:40,936
That's what they said, "maybe", which
sounds suspiciously like "no" to me.

122
00:13:41,103 --> 00:13:43,814
There's one of them now.

123
00:13:47,442 --> 00:13:49,236
I'm not dead yet.

124
00:13:50,237 --> 00:13:55,325
I am in a hospital, which means
that I'm not in my office,

125
00:13:55,492 --> 00:13:57,869
which means
I don't know what's going on.

126
00:13:58,036 --> 00:14:01,039
- I need you there.
- Where?

127
00:14:01,206 --> 00:14:05,043
- In my office, doing my job.
- Wait a minute...

128
00:14:05,210 --> 00:14:08,547
I hate not knowing
what's going on, you know that.

129
00:14:08,714 --> 00:14:11,717
I wouldn't know
how to do your job, sir.

130
00:14:11,883 --> 00:14:16,179
You've been around.
You've been to the White House.

131
00:14:16,346 --> 00:14:20,183
- Once. I hated it.
- No, you didn't.

132
00:14:21,268 --> 00:14:25,313
Want to know about politics
in Washington? Four words.

133
00:14:25,480 --> 00:14:28,316
"Watch your back, Jack."

134
00:14:33,155 --> 00:14:38,660
Bobby, you should be the first
to know, or the third or fourth.

135
00:14:38,827 --> 00:14:42,331
Ryan is to be
Acting Deputy Director, Intelligence.

136
00:14:42,497 --> 00:14:47,836
It will be a provisional appointment,
of course, until James recovers.

137
00:14:48,003 --> 00:14:51,631
Get him up to speed
on our aid programme to Colombia.

138
00:14:51,798 --> 00:14:56,595
He must talk the Oversight Committee
out of another $75 million.

139
00:14:56,762 --> 00:15:00,349
And not make a complete fool
out of himself.

140
00:15:02,267 --> 00:15:04,394
What about the Hardin murders?

141
00:15:04,561 --> 00:15:08,315
I'm on it. The President's calling
for a full-court press.

142
00:15:08,482 --> 00:15:13,528
So, you guys are going to be
working together hand in hand.

143
00:15:14,738 --> 00:15:16,907
That's great.

144
00:15:31,838 --> 00:15:36,093
Margaret, why don't we
leave all his things?

145
00:15:36,259 --> 00:15:37,844
OK, yeah.

146
00:15:50,190 --> 00:15:53,360
Ryan. I can't believe itl

147
00:15:53,527 --> 00:15:57,197
He's not a team player,
is thatwhat you're saying?

148
00:15:57,364 --> 00:15:59,408
He's a Boy Scout.

149
00:16:00,325 --> 00:16:05,831
A goddamn Boy Scout. Believes in
loyalty, cleanliness and knot-tying.

150
00:16:05,998 --> 00:16:08,083
So leave him out of it.

151
00:16:08,250 --> 00:16:12,295
He's the Deputy Director of
Intelligence. That will be tricky.

152
00:16:12,462 --> 00:16:14,923
What does he need to know?

153
00:16:15,090 --> 00:16:21,513
Nothing. He needs to know nothing.
He's going to know nothing.

154
00:16:21,680 --> 00:16:24,516
I want a copy
of the President's authorisation

155
00:16:24,683 --> 00:16:27,602
of this new action
against the cartels.

156
00:16:28,645 --> 00:16:32,149
- You want what?
- You heard me.

157
00:16:33,483 --> 00:16:35,277
He doesn't know about it.

158
00:16:37,237 --> 00:16:43,410
Let me explain it to you very simply.
This is your deal, not mine.

159
00:16:43,577 --> 00:16:48,665
Unless I have written authorisation,
this thing is over before it begins.

160
00:16:48,832 --> 00:16:53,920
I'm not going to be the only one left
without a chair when the music stops.

161
00:17:34,628 --> 00:17:38,006
"Reciprocity."
That's a clever name for it.

162
00:17:38,173 --> 00:17:42,636
Revenge is a very, very, very
dangerous motivation.

163
00:17:44,221 --> 00:17:50,394
Are you able to handle this operation
or not? I'm looking for a yes or no.

164
00:17:50,560 --> 00:17:53,480
You're looking for a political mess.

165
00:17:53,647 --> 00:17:56,483
- Yes or no?
- Is that what they want?

166
00:17:56,650 --> 00:18:01,196
They want what every first-term
administration wants. A second term.

167
00:18:02,531 --> 00:18:05,909
I don't imagine the boys on the Hill
have approved this.

168
00:18:11,581 --> 00:18:13,667
Have they?

169
00:18:15,544 --> 00:18:18,380
Is that a "no"?

170
00:18:23,593 --> 00:18:25,345
Shit.

171
00:18:26,138 --> 00:18:31,393
I want the money in my account
before I move an inch.

172
00:18:31,560 --> 00:18:33,103
You got it.

173
00:18:33,270 --> 00:18:35,522
- I need a Comsat link.
- You got it.

174
00:18:35,689 --> 00:18:39,026
- An insertion team.
- You can have a brigade.

175
00:18:39,192 --> 00:18:42,487
Just 12 men who understand
discretionary warfare.

176
00:18:42,654 --> 00:18:45,824
Special Ops. Spanish speaking.

177
00:18:53,457 --> 00:18:56,209
- How are you today, sir?
- Very well.

178
00:18:56,376 --> 00:18:59,463
- The purpose of your visit?
- Business.

179
00:18:59,629 --> 00:19:02,549
- What business are you in?
- I sell tractors.

180
00:19:02,716 --> 00:19:05,927
Well, I build them, then I sell them.

181
00:19:06,094 --> 00:19:10,098
- And how long will you be staying?
- A few days.

182
00:19:37,876 --> 00:19:41,713
I know it's a risk,
but what's the alternative?

183
00:19:41,880 --> 00:19:46,176
Zapping a retina with 6,000 rads
of cobalt? Not a pretty picture.

184
00:19:46,343 --> 00:19:49,638
Prettier than a tumour
spreading in the cranial sack.

185
00:19:49,805 --> 00:19:53,016
- What is her name?
- I'm trying to have lunch.

186
00:19:54,184 --> 00:19:57,688
Listen... Hungry?

187
00:19:57,854 --> 00:20:01,733
- Starved.
- We could forget about lunch.

188
00:20:01,900 --> 00:20:07,364
- We did that last time, remember?
- Do I remember? Do you?

189
00:20:08,699 --> 00:20:12,494
- Vaguely.
- Maybe I should refresh your memory.

190
00:20:14,871 --> 00:20:17,874
- Maybe you should.
- Yourtable is ready now.

191
00:20:18,041 --> 00:20:21,086
- We don't need it. I'll get a cab.
- Moira?

192
00:20:21,253 --> 00:20:26,758
- Hi! How are you? How's Jack?
- He's great, just great.

193
00:20:26,925 --> 00:20:29,928
- You still with the FBI?
- The Director's office.

194
00:20:30,095 --> 00:20:32,597
- Who was that?
- My new friend.

195
00:20:32,764 --> 00:20:35,684
Seסor Roberto Landa.

196
00:20:35,851 --> 00:20:39,896
- Doesn't he look like Jack?
- Does he? I can't quite see.

197
00:20:40,063 --> 00:20:44,818
- Only Latin.
- A Latin Jack? This I have to see.

198
00:20:45,819 --> 00:20:48,196
I have to go. Bye.

199
00:20:49,948 --> 00:20:54,703
Well, we know it's not piracy.
Pirates steal boats.

200
00:20:54,870 --> 00:20:59,666
They had plane tickets to Bogota
the morning afterthe killings.

201
00:20:59,833 --> 00:21:01,501
- Hey, Dan.
- How's it going?

202
00:21:01,668 --> 00:21:05,130
We're sneaking up on a motive.
Dan Murray, Bureau.

203
00:21:05,297 --> 00:21:08,175
- Ralph Williams, DEA.
- Said anything yet?

204
00:21:08,342 --> 00:21:12,721
- Yeah. "We're innocent."
- Till the DA offers them a deal.

205
00:21:12,888 --> 00:21:16,308
He already has.
Regular or extra crispy?

206
00:21:16,475 --> 00:21:20,062
Either referring to fried chicken
or the electric chair.

207
00:21:20,687 --> 00:21:22,773
Are you picturing a hit?

208
00:21:22,939 --> 00:21:27,069
On a respectable American
businessman and his family?

209
00:21:28,070 --> 00:21:31,073
You're assuming he's respectable.

210
00:21:39,539 --> 00:21:45,212
We have memos, letters,
credit card statements,

211
00:21:45,379 --> 00:21:50,801
phone bills, everything
you could need to break his code.

212
00:21:50,967 --> 00:21:54,012
- What's this?
- Old high school yearbook.

213
00:21:54,179 --> 00:21:58,058
- Sweethearts, football team...
- You think?

214
00:21:58,225 --> 00:22:03,105
- I don't know.
- OK, let's see what we've got.

215
00:22:03,271 --> 00:22:06,358
- No cream?
- There wasn't any.

216
00:22:06,525 --> 00:22:10,320
Let's startwith birthdays.
Bet your ATM code is your birthday.

217
00:22:10,487 --> 00:22:13,156
- Close.
- In reverse?

218
00:22:15,033 --> 00:22:17,911
Alright, his birthday is...

219
00:22:19,037 --> 00:22:24,292
That would be too easy, wouldn't it?
Let's try it in reverse.

220
00:22:24,459 --> 00:22:27,212
No. His wife's?

221
00:22:28,255 --> 00:22:30,048
No. His son's?

222
00:22:30,215 --> 00:22:32,551
- This could take...
- Months.

223
00:22:32,718 --> 00:22:34,678
Son's in reverse. This is for you.

224
00:22:37,139 --> 00:22:40,100
No. Wife's in reverse.

225
00:22:40,267 --> 00:22:42,477
No. Daughter's in reverse.

226
00:22:42,644 --> 00:22:45,689
You've got to change your ATM code.

227
00:22:48,066 --> 00:22:50,861
No. Wife, daughter. Nothing.

228
00:22:53,322 --> 00:22:54,698
Got it.

229
00:22:54,865 --> 00:22:56,908
I got it!

230
00:23:07,294 --> 00:23:11,298
Wife's birth month,
daughter's day, son's year.

231
00:23:11,465 --> 00:23:14,217
But not in reverse. Sorry.

232
00:23:21,767 --> 00:23:24,686
Print me out that one.

233
00:23:24,853 --> 00:23:26,772
Good boy.

234
00:23:27,439 --> 00:23:31,943
Three years ago, Hardin received
an infusion of foreign capital

235
00:23:32,110 --> 00:23:37,032
which he invested in 20 major
shopping centres in the US.

236
00:23:37,199 --> 00:23:41,828
In the middle of the recession,
he posted record profits,

237
00:23:41,995 --> 00:23:46,500
at least to the IRS, who he feared
more than his own partners.

238
00:23:46,667 --> 00:23:50,962
To them, according to the stockholder
statements he was giving them,

239
00:23:51,129 --> 00:23:54,299
the shopping centres
weren't doing nearly as well.

240
00:23:54,466 --> 00:23:58,804
But he wasjust skimming
most of the profits, $650 million,

241
00:23:58,970 --> 00:24:02,474
and putting it in accounts
in Luxembourg, Panama

242
00:24:02,641 --> 00:24:04,726
and the Cayman Islands.

243
00:24:06,144 --> 00:24:08,230
They killed him for it.

244
00:24:08,397 --> 00:24:10,315
Who?

245
00:24:10,482 --> 00:24:13,694
- His partners.
- Who were his partners?

246
00:24:13,860 --> 00:24:20,242
It seems clear that he was laundering
money for the Colombian drug cartels.

247
00:24:20,409 --> 00:24:26,248
Jesus! I knew the man for 40 years.
We went to school together.

248
00:24:27,165 --> 00:24:29,668
We almostwent
into business together.

249
00:24:29,835 --> 00:24:32,462
That would have been good.

250
00:24:34,047 --> 00:24:37,050
The press is going to
have a field day with this.

251
00:24:37,217 --> 00:24:41,847
- No one outside this room knows.
- They will. They always do.

252
00:24:42,014 --> 00:24:45,892
It will come up, you're right
about that. When it does,

253
00:24:46,059 --> 00:24:51,565
we'll downplay your relationship
with Hardin somehow.

254
00:24:54,192 --> 00:24:55,902
- What?
- What?

255
00:24:56,069 --> 00:24:59,781
- We'll defuse it.
- Do you disagree?

256
00:24:59,948 --> 00:25:01,450
No.

257
00:25:01,616 --> 00:25:06,413
Well, actually, yes. I would go
in the other direction.

258
00:25:06,580 --> 00:25:11,960
If a reporter asked if you and Hardin
were friends, I'd say "good friends".

259
00:25:12,127 --> 00:25:16,840
If they asked if you were good
friends, I'd say"lifelong friends".

260
00:25:17,007 --> 00:25:22,721
Give them no place to go,
nothing to report. No story.

261
00:25:24,973 --> 00:25:29,728
I mean, it's no sense in
defusing a bomb after it's already...

262
00:25:31,021 --> 00:25:33,565
...it's already gone off.

263
00:25:57,089 --> 00:25:58,632
- Damn!
- Shit!

264
00:26:00,467 --> 00:26:02,052
Do you see him?

265
00:26:03,303 --> 00:26:07,099
Alright. Move your team
two metres to the left.

266
00:26:10,560 --> 00:26:13,271
That's it. Stop.

267
00:26:13,438 --> 00:26:18,026
Touch that light-coloured grass.
Sniper at your feet.

268
00:26:18,902 --> 00:26:20,737
Nothing here, Sergeant Major.

269
00:26:20,904 --> 00:26:24,199
- Damn!
- He is good.

270
00:26:40,966 --> 00:26:44,094
Thatwas close.
How's he moving so fast?

271
00:26:49,850 --> 00:26:53,979
I see him. Come in.
Straight in. Now. Run!

272
00:26:55,230 --> 00:26:57,316
Keep coming.

273
00:26:58,984 --> 00:27:03,613
Stop. To your left. To your left.

274
00:27:04,281 --> 00:27:08,493
And stop. Sniper at your feet.

275
00:27:10,162 --> 00:27:12,581
What is it?

276
00:27:15,334 --> 00:27:17,085
He had lunch here.

277
00:27:18,045 --> 00:27:19,921
McDonald's quarter-pounder.

278
00:27:20,088 --> 00:27:22,007
With cheese.

279
00:27:23,592 --> 00:27:25,093
Damn.

280
00:27:31,141 --> 00:27:33,769
- Damn!
- That's four.

281
00:27:34,895 --> 00:27:38,899
Alright, you won this one.
Come on out!

282
00:27:40,692 --> 00:27:43,862
Soldier, how did you get
that close to me?

283
00:27:44,029 --> 00:27:49,409
Sniper approached instructor by being
a sneaky bastard, Sergeant Major!

284
00:27:49,576 --> 00:27:53,664
Do you know the fine for littering
in California, Chavez?

285
00:27:53,830 --> 00:27:56,291
Yes, sir!

286
00:27:58,710 --> 00:28:02,422
I saw you on the sniper course.
You looked good.

287
00:28:02,589 --> 00:28:06,259
- Just about finished here, Sergeant?
- Yes, sir.

288
00:28:06,426 --> 00:28:10,389
Looking forward to taking
some leave with your wife and kids?

289
00:28:11,223 --> 00:28:15,185
- Don't have any wife or kids, sir.
- What do you have?

290
00:28:16,144 --> 00:28:22,651
You don't call anybody often, you
don't write or receive many letters.

291
00:28:25,237 --> 00:28:27,990
Who are you, sir, if I may ask?

292
00:28:28,156 --> 00:28:32,744
Mr Clark and I are putting together
a mission. My team is a part of it.

293
00:28:32,911 --> 00:28:37,666
You'd be gone up to six months,
after which, if you're not dead,

294
00:28:37,833 --> 00:28:41,336
you'd have your choice
of assignments in Special Ops.

295
00:28:58,020 --> 00:29:03,483
...defusing an issue that was
snowballing into another scandal.

296
00:29:03,650 --> 00:29:07,904
"The New York Times"reports that
you and Hardin were good friends.

297
00:29:08,071 --> 00:29:12,200
No, not good friends.
We were lifelong friends.

298
00:29:12,367 --> 00:29:16,246
I said that. I said that.

299
00:29:18,206 --> 00:29:20,459
I told him to say that.

300
00:29:20,625 --> 00:29:24,338
- What?
- I didn't say anything.

301
00:29:24,504 --> 00:29:28,258
- But you were thinking something.
- No.

302
00:29:28,425 --> 00:29:33,388
I was just distracted by the trouble
you were having with your ensemble.

303
00:29:34,306 --> 00:29:39,144
Well, it's not every day
you have to look trustworthy.

304
00:29:39,311 --> 00:29:43,106
- Who told who to say what?
- It's not important.

305
00:29:44,149 --> 00:29:46,860
- The President?
- Yeah.

306
00:29:47,027 --> 00:29:51,490
Mom says she makes more money
than the President.

307
00:29:51,657 --> 00:29:54,993
She's probably right. Bye.

308
00:30:03,335 --> 00:30:07,547
Thank you, Dr Ryan, for the
information you've shared with us.

309
00:30:08,340 --> 00:30:11,968
- Thank you, Senator.
- We have to help the Colombians

310
00:30:12,135 --> 00:30:16,598
in their struggle to curtail
the drug cartels' activities.

311
00:30:16,765 --> 00:30:22,270
However, I'm confused.
How do you see additional funds

312
00:30:22,437 --> 00:30:25,983
advancing this programme
from the failure that it is?

313
00:30:26,149 --> 00:30:30,487
- You see what I'm getting at?
- No, I'm afraid I don't.

314
00:30:30,654 --> 00:30:34,157
You said this effort would be
totally benign on our part.

315
00:30:34,324 --> 00:30:38,870
Our assistance is limited
to supply and advice only.

316
00:30:39,037 --> 00:30:40,789
I've read that.

317
00:30:40,956 --> 00:30:45,127
I've also read a similar finding
written 35 years ago

318
00:30:45,293 --> 00:30:49,798
regarding a little-thought-of
sliver ofjungle in Southeast Asia.

319
00:30:49,965 --> 00:30:56,096
You're comparing our request
for anti-drug funds to Vietnam?

320
00:30:56,263 --> 00:31:00,434
I'm comparing it to every time
a committee such as this is asked

321
00:31:00,600 --> 00:31:05,147
to render judgement
based on less than all the facts.

322
00:31:08,066 --> 00:31:11,069
I'm afraid I don't know
what to say to that.

323
00:31:11,236 --> 00:31:14,448
You can assure us
that we have all the facts.

324
00:31:14,614 --> 00:31:16,158
I thought I had.

325
00:31:16,325 --> 00:31:21,913
You can further assure us then
that this increase in funds

326
00:31:22,080 --> 00:31:25,584
will not be used for
any covert military action.

327
00:31:25,751 --> 00:31:28,962
I don't know how
you're getting to this.

328
00:31:29,212 --> 00:31:32,549
Long experience, sir.

329
00:31:32,716 --> 00:31:34,843
No troops then?

330
00:31:35,010 --> 00:31:40,766
I enunciate that clearly because I
don't want there to be any mistake.

331
00:31:40,932 --> 00:31:42,642
No troops.

332
00:31:43,602 --> 00:31:46,563
You could say
I have your word on that?

333
00:31:46,730 --> 00:31:49,941
You could indeed, because you do.

334
00:32:04,748 --> 00:32:11,421
Listen up! Dog tags.
Take 'em off, pass 'em forward.

335
00:32:11,588 --> 00:32:17,344
Check your pockets for anything
that can be used for identification.

336
00:32:25,268 --> 00:32:26,645
We're feet dry.

337
00:32:40,450 --> 00:32:43,662
LZ in sight. Get ready.

338
00:32:43,829 --> 00:32:46,915
Good luck, boys. Go get 'em.

339
00:32:50,794 --> 00:32:53,005
OK, let's take her down now.

340
00:33:09,354 --> 00:33:11,690
Go, go, go!

341
00:34:39,861 --> 00:34:41,530
Hey, Bob.

342
00:34:43,615 --> 00:34:46,159
- How you doing?
- Good, sir.

343
00:34:47,160 --> 00:34:49,287
Good to see you.

344
00:34:55,210 --> 00:34:58,714
- Morning, Jack.
- Ryan! Come on in.

345
00:34:58,880 --> 00:35:01,758
- Do you know everyone?
- Yes, yes.

346
00:35:01,925 --> 00:35:06,096
- Coffee? Bagel?
- Coffee. Black.

347
00:35:06,263 --> 00:35:09,349
- How's the family?
- Good, sir.

348
00:35:09,516 --> 00:35:13,186
- When do I meet the other Dr Ryan?
- She's dying to meet you, sir.

349
00:35:13,353 --> 00:35:15,480
Good, good. Sit down.

350
00:35:17,899 --> 00:35:19,651
Thank you.

351
00:35:19,818 --> 00:35:22,029
So.

352
00:35:22,195 --> 00:35:26,325
- The cash is still there?
- Sir?

353
00:35:26,491 --> 00:35:30,746
- In Hardin's offshore accounts.
- $650 million.

354
00:35:30,912 --> 00:35:32,998
- And change.
- And change.

355
00:35:33,165 --> 00:35:36,710
- And we have the account numbers.
- Yes, sir.

356
00:35:36,877 --> 00:35:40,839
Well, what are we waiting for?
Let's get it.

357
00:35:41,006 --> 00:35:43,884
- Let's get it?
- Let's turn this thing around.

358
00:35:44,051 --> 00:35:46,219
$650 million and change.

359
00:35:46,386 --> 00:35:51,308
It's worth ten times that
in political capital.

360
00:35:52,392 --> 00:35:55,062
What?

361
00:35:55,228 --> 00:36:02,903
Well, this connection between
Hardin and the cartels is a theory.

362
00:36:03,070 --> 00:36:05,489
- Theory?
- Atheory of mine.

363
00:36:05,656 --> 00:36:09,326
- It's a theory?
- Well, I know the money is there.

364
00:36:09,493 --> 00:36:14,289
But who exactly Hardin
was working for, I don't know.

365
00:36:14,456 --> 00:36:20,170
I think we would have to establish
that before we could seize the money.

366
00:36:22,923 --> 00:36:26,218
So go down there. Establish it.

367
00:36:26,385 --> 00:36:29,054
- Go where?
- Colombia.

368
00:36:30,806 --> 00:36:33,350
Who, me?

369
00:36:36,645 --> 00:36:41,525
I leave you alone for two weeks,
and you walk into a big bear trap.

370
00:36:41,692 --> 00:36:43,735
What was I thinking?

371
00:36:43,902 --> 00:36:50,283
You were thinking about impressing
the President. You shouldn't do that.

372
00:36:50,450 --> 00:36:53,787
- November.
- January.

373
00:36:53,954 --> 00:36:55,747
Of last year.

374
00:36:58,709 --> 00:37:03,422
There's a guy down there,
at least he used to be... Clark.

375
00:37:04,381 --> 00:37:06,800
We go way back. Good man.

376
00:37:06,967 --> 00:37:09,928
If you hit a brick wall, look him up.

377
00:37:11,013 --> 00:37:13,348
Admiral Greer?

378
00:37:13,515 --> 00:37:16,935
- Chemotherapy.
- Oh, shit.

379
00:37:17,728 --> 00:37:19,938
Here we go again.

380
00:37:21,231 --> 00:37:23,567
How's Ritter behaving?

381
00:37:23,734 --> 00:37:27,446
Ritter's Ritter.
He's leaving me alone.

382
00:37:27,612 --> 00:37:31,783
Are you sure?
Watch him like a hawk.

383
00:37:31,950 --> 00:37:34,202
- How are you feeling today?
- OK.

384
00:37:34,369 --> 00:37:40,042
We'll get you in a room, give you
warm blankets, get you lying down.

385
00:37:40,208 --> 00:37:43,837
Then we'll get you back
to your room and comfortable.

386
00:38:38,308 --> 00:38:41,645
Variable, this is Knife,
stand by to copy, over.

387
00:38:44,606 --> 00:38:47,776
Variable, this is Knife,
stand by to copy, over.

388
00:38:47,943 --> 00:38:52,030
Knife, this is Variable,
your signal is five by five, over.

389
00:38:55,325 --> 00:38:57,327
Clear.

390
00:39:20,892 --> 00:39:23,270
The chicken is in the pot. Over.

391
00:39:25,105 --> 00:39:28,066
- Cook it.
- Roger that.

392
00:39:44,499 --> 00:39:47,794
Honey? I'm late.

393
00:39:48,712 --> 00:39:52,049
- Bye.
- Have a good trip.

394
00:39:53,133 --> 00:39:56,011
I'm not gonna say it.

395
00:39:56,178 --> 00:39:58,013
Don't.

396
00:39:58,180 --> 00:40:00,265
Be careful.

397
00:40:28,043 --> 00:40:34,633
Local time is, well, actually, it's
the same as Washington, 11:16am.

398
00:40:34,800 --> 00:40:38,303
Temperature
is 69 degrees Fahrenheit...

399
00:40:44,768 --> 00:40:47,062
Dr Ryan!

400
00:40:56,822 --> 00:41:00,117
DEASpecial Agent Jean Fowler.
How you doing?

401
00:41:00,283 --> 00:41:02,494
- First time in Bogota?
- Yeah.

402
00:41:02,661 --> 00:41:07,082
Let's not stand here
and let someone take a shot at you.

403
00:41:07,249 --> 00:41:09,209
Come on, sir, let's go.

404
00:41:23,598 --> 00:41:27,269
- And these two are?
- They're brothers.

405
00:41:29,980 --> 00:41:34,276
Don't do that. Give Dr Ryan
a bit more air back here, please.

406
00:41:34,443 --> 00:41:36,528
Bulletproof.

407
00:41:43,785 --> 00:41:47,706
We don't have a picture.
Escobedo's intelligence officer.

408
00:41:47,873 --> 00:41:51,001
We don't have a name either,
but we know he exists.

409
00:41:52,002 --> 00:41:54,880
The invisible man?

410
00:41:55,630 --> 00:41:58,300
Gently, gently, with your hands.

411
00:41:58,467 --> 00:42:01,720
Luis, put your hands together.

412
00:42:02,429 --> 00:42:05,349
No, your hands together!

413
00:42:08,352 --> 00:42:10,854
Luis, watch the canter.

414
00:42:12,105 --> 00:42:15,108
Yes, very good.

415
00:42:19,237 --> 00:42:20,489
Yes?

416
00:42:23,325 --> 00:42:24,951
We lost another plane.

417
00:42:28,288 --> 00:42:29,873
OK.

418
00:42:32,918 --> 00:42:36,922
- Who is doing this?
- If I had to guess...

419
00:42:37,089 --> 00:42:40,676
No, I did not ask you to guess.
I can guess.

420
00:42:41,551 --> 00:42:44,262
Someone has been talking
to the drug police.

421
00:42:44,429 --> 00:42:49,601
Impossible. If anyone spoke to
the police, I'd be the first to know.

422
00:42:49,768 --> 00:42:51,853
Ernesto?

423
00:42:53,271 --> 00:42:58,402
Is one of the others trying to ruin
me after what I did to the American?

424
00:42:58,568 --> 00:43:04,032
I guess that wasn't quite the
deterrent you thought itwould be.

425
00:43:04,199 --> 00:43:06,785
Find out who it is.

426
00:43:14,292 --> 00:43:18,088
What do you make of this, Colonel?

427
00:43:18,255 --> 00:43:20,340
An opportunity.

428
00:43:22,467 --> 00:43:24,886
An opportunity, Sipo.

429
00:43:39,109 --> 00:43:42,863
- Good afternoon.
- Messages, please?

430
00:43:44,197 --> 00:43:48,785
- Dr Ryan?
- Clark? Sorry I'm late.

431
00:43:48,952 --> 00:43:51,496
I've got ten minutes.

432
00:43:53,707 --> 00:43:57,794
I'm positive Hardin was tied
into the cartels. It's drug money.

433
00:43:57,961 --> 00:44:01,882
- But you can't prove it.
- So far.

434
00:44:03,300 --> 00:44:06,678
- Mind if I ask you a question?
- No.

435
00:44:06,845 --> 00:44:12,851
Why are you telling me all this? I've
been out of the game for a long time.

436
00:44:15,062 --> 00:44:20,484
I was told that you were wired, and
that you knew the town and people.

437
00:44:20,651 --> 00:44:24,154
- That you were a player.
- Who told you that?

438
00:44:25,947 --> 00:44:27,866
Jim Greer.

439
00:44:29,660 --> 00:44:31,328
How's he doing?

440
00:44:34,456 --> 00:44:37,250
He's not good.

441
00:44:38,377 --> 00:44:40,295
He has cancer.

442
00:44:40,462 --> 00:44:42,798
Terminal.

443
00:44:44,633 --> 00:44:48,804
- He's a good man.
- The best.

444
00:44:55,060 --> 00:44:57,521
You a coffee drinker, Dr Ryan?

445
00:45:00,691 --> 00:45:04,569
- Yeah, I like coffee.
- Try the Lindo brand.

446
00:45:04,736 --> 00:45:08,240
- Lindo?
- I think you'll like it.

447
00:45:14,204 --> 00:45:17,791
Mr President,
I've got some good news.

448
00:45:17,958 --> 00:45:22,838
Hardin's partner here was someone
you may know of. Ernesto Escobedo.

449
00:45:23,005 --> 00:45:28,385
- Escobedo? It figures.
- Is this another of your theories?

450
00:45:28,552 --> 00:45:34,599
No, sir. We can call this one fact.
Escobedo, like every drug lord here,

451
00:45:34,766 --> 00:45:40,439
also had legitimate businesses.
Hardin was doing business with these.

452
00:45:40,605 --> 00:45:45,902
Importing, among other things,
coffee, which means nothing,

453
00:45:46,069 --> 00:45:52,576
but he was paying too much
for this coffee. $6,200 a pound.

454
00:45:52,743 --> 00:45:56,288
- That's expensive coffee.
- I'd have to agree.

455
00:45:56,455 --> 00:45:59,291
This is good news.
I think this does it.

456
00:45:59,458 --> 00:46:03,420
Sir, I also have some other news
which is not so good.

457
00:46:04,379 --> 00:46:05,964
Oh, God.

458
00:46:07,299 --> 00:46:12,095
The DEAfeels that the government
here would want the seized funds.

459
00:46:12,262 --> 00:46:17,142
- Or at least a large portion.
- This is our money.

460
00:46:17,309 --> 00:46:21,104
- We found it.
- We can try telling them that.

461
00:46:21,271 --> 00:46:24,691
Try? Tell them.
Or don't tell them, I don't care.

462
00:46:24,858 --> 00:46:29,571
- Sir, with all due respect...
- This is our money, tell them that.

463
00:46:29,738 --> 00:46:34,826
I wouldn't know what to say or
where to start. I'm not a negotiator.

464
00:46:34,993 --> 00:46:37,245
You know someone
in their government?

465
00:46:37,412 --> 00:46:40,082
I went to school
with their Attorney General.

466
00:46:40,248 --> 00:46:46,046
Jacobs will come down.
He'll negotiate. This is our money.

467
00:46:46,213 --> 00:46:47,255
Thank...

468
00:46:48,924 --> 00:46:51,009
Thank you.

469
00:46:53,887 --> 00:46:55,973
I hate this job.

470
00:48:13,842 --> 00:48:16,303
Eyes up!

471
00:48:18,430 --> 00:48:20,641
Demo team, up!

472
00:48:27,731 --> 00:48:29,983
Fire in the hole!

473
00:48:34,488 --> 00:48:37,908
Let's go, let's go!
Move out! Go, go, go!

474
00:48:40,619 --> 00:48:41,703
Down! Down!

475
00:48:59,388 --> 00:49:01,890
Whoever did this is dead.

476
00:49:03,266 --> 00:49:07,854
Whoever did this to me is dead!

477
00:49:08,021 --> 00:49:12,943
Do you hear me?
Are you listening to me?

478
00:49:27,749 --> 00:49:31,294
Mr Jacobs, could you sign these
before you leave?

479
00:49:32,754 --> 00:49:38,010
Moira, why don't you
call in sick tomorrow?

480
00:49:38,176 --> 00:49:41,555
And the next day.
I won't tell anybody.

481
00:49:41,722 --> 00:49:45,183
Even when you're not here
there's plenty to do.

482
00:49:45,350 --> 00:49:49,688
- Your itinerary.
- You're arguing with me about this?

483
00:49:49,855 --> 00:49:53,525
You work too hard. Adiףs.

