486
00:50:40,280 --> 00:50:44,117
I think he's on the factory floor.
Hold on.

487
00:50:49,373 --> 00:50:53,293
- Yes?
- A Moira Wolfson is calling.

488
00:50:54,336 --> 00:50:59,216
I told her you were
on the factory floor. Go ahead.

489
00:50:59,383 --> 00:51:02,594
- Moira!
- Hi.

490
00:51:02,761 --> 00:51:04,930
You free the next couple of days?

491
00:51:05,097 --> 00:51:08,058
- Next couple of days?
- I am.

492
00:51:08,767 --> 00:51:11,436
My boss is leaving the country.

493
00:51:13,271 --> 00:51:18,318
- Can I call you later?
- Alright, call me at home. Bye.

494
00:51:26,994 --> 00:51:33,208
Good afternoon.
Good news in the fight against drugs.

495
00:51:33,375 --> 00:51:37,170
An investigation
by the Department of Justice

496
00:51:37,337 --> 00:51:42,009
has identified several
bank accounts from Luxembourg

497
00:51:42,175 --> 00:51:46,221
to the Cayman Islands,
used for laundering drug money

498
00:51:46,388 --> 00:51:51,810
on an unprecedented scale.
With five foreign governments

499
00:51:51,977 --> 00:51:55,355
we have taken steps
to seize those funds

500
00:51:55,522 --> 00:52:00,485
- which amount to over $650 million.
- Shit.

501
00:52:00,652 --> 00:52:05,824
Also to seize 20 real estate
joint-venture investments in the US

502
00:52:05,991 --> 00:52:11,872
which were the primary agencies
in the laundering operations.

503
00:52:12,039 --> 00:52:15,792
You did say $650 million?

504
00:52:15,959 --> 00:52:19,755
That's right.
$650 million. And change.

505
00:52:19,921 --> 00:52:22,299
They're stealing my money!

506
00:52:22,466 --> 00:52:27,471
- What's our take?
- It's hard to say at the moment.

507
00:52:27,638 --> 00:52:32,601
No, it isn't. You're stealing my
money. I made it, you're stealing it!

508
00:52:33,393 --> 00:52:39,024
Mr President, can we speak with
FBI Director Jacobs about this?

509
00:52:39,191 --> 00:52:43,070
- Jacobs is not available.
- Someone will die for this.

510
00:52:43,236 --> 00:52:48,283
He's personally involved in the
investigation and is pretty busy.

511
00:52:58,960 --> 00:53:04,091
This avenue has to be avoided.
They'll be coming from the airport.

512
00:53:04,257 --> 00:53:08,303
Up Avenida Aeropuerto El Dorado
all the way to Gran America.

513
00:53:08,470 --> 00:53:13,392
Santa Fe's our spot. As much as
I'd love to be here for this,

514
00:53:13,558 --> 00:53:19,648
I have to take care of business in
Washington, tying up loose ends.

515
00:53:28,365 --> 00:53:31,952
Hello?
Don't hang up, don't hang up.

516
00:53:33,578 --> 00:53:38,125
- Hello?
- The machine is still on, Moira.

517
00:54:10,699 --> 00:54:14,578
- Emil, good to see you.
- Andy, good to see you.

518
00:54:14,745 --> 00:54:19,458
- Agent Murray, Ambassador Ferris.
- Hi, good to see you.

519
00:54:19,624 --> 00:54:24,713
- This will bring you up to date.
- Alright, let's go.

520
00:54:37,434 --> 00:54:42,147
- How's the food?
- It's like Mexican food.

521
00:54:42,314 --> 00:54:45,776
- You hate Mexican food.
- I hate Mexican food.

522
00:55:21,645 --> 00:55:24,022
- Hi.
- Hello.

523
00:55:24,189 --> 00:55:29,111
All my secretary knows about America
is what she reads inPeoplemagazine.

524
00:55:29,277 --> 00:55:32,864
- How's the place?
- Come inside and find out.

525
00:55:40,831 --> 00:55:43,834
It's awful.

526
00:55:45,711 --> 00:55:48,046
Isn't it?

527
00:56:11,111 --> 00:56:13,572
So I take it you shouldn't
drink the water?

528
00:56:15,282 --> 00:56:20,162
They put water in your room,
but I'd stick to the bottled stuff.

529
00:57:09,628 --> 00:57:12,631
So what do you brush your teeth with?

530
00:57:12,798 --> 00:57:17,386
You use the bottled water, or you'll
be in the can all yourtime here.

531
00:57:25,018 --> 00:57:27,521
The hold-up
was a government connection?

532
00:57:27,688 --> 00:57:29,690
Yeah, that's the connection.

533
00:58:21,950 --> 00:58:23,994
Back up! Back up!

534
00:58:30,250 --> 00:58:32,586
- Step on it!
- Stay down. Stay down.

535
00:58:47,059 --> 00:58:49,227
Damn it! Back up!

536
00:58:52,898 --> 00:58:55,901
- Let's go! Let's go!
- Take it easy, Andy.

537
00:58:56,401 --> 00:58:59,988
Got to keep moving. Go, Jack!

538
00:59:16,171 --> 00:59:18,632
Incoming!

539
00:59:57,504 --> 00:59:58,672
Dan!

540
01:00:30,329 --> 01:00:32,331
Dan! Dan!

541
01:00:43,050 --> 01:00:45,886
We can't stay here!

542
01:00:47,763 --> 01:00:50,182
The car! Is it running?

543
01:00:50,349 --> 01:00:52,351
It's running!

544
01:00:52,517 --> 01:00:57,522
The smoke will give us cover.
It's our only chance. I got him.

545
01:00:57,689 --> 01:01:00,609
Make for the driver's side.
Ready? Go!

546
01:01:11,328 --> 01:01:14,623
- Get in!
- Go! Go!

547
01:02:17,936 --> 01:02:20,439
Housekeeping.

548
01:02:30,240 --> 01:02:32,701
Oh, excuse me, ma'am.

549
01:02:41,877 --> 01:02:45,380
- Do you have a call for Dr Ryan?
- Just a moment.

550
01:02:45,547 --> 01:02:47,299
...in Bogota today.

551
01:02:47,466 --> 01:02:52,346
Ten members of the escort party
were also killed and eight wounded.

552
01:02:52,512 --> 01:02:56,224
Five of the dead
were security personnel...

553
01:02:56,391 --> 01:03:01,229
- Cathy?
- Don't tell me you're in this.

554
01:03:01,396 --> 01:03:05,317
Right in the middle of it.
Honey, Dan was killed.

555
01:03:05,484 --> 01:03:07,694
Dan Murray.

556
01:03:10,697 --> 01:03:14,451
He was ten feet away.
There was nothing I could do.

557
01:03:16,453 --> 01:03:19,665
- I'm coming home.
- Thank God.

558
01:03:19,831 --> 01:03:22,417
I love you.

559
01:03:27,047 --> 01:03:30,467
- Wasn't his going there a secret?
- It was.

560
01:03:30,634 --> 01:03:35,180
- Then I don't get it. What happened?
- Nobody knows.

561
01:03:35,347 --> 01:03:39,768
- How stupid are these people?
- They believe they can do anything.

562
01:03:39,935 --> 01:03:43,105
You know what? They're wrong.

563
01:03:43,271 --> 01:03:45,899
- Yes, sir.
- They're wrong.

564
01:03:47,609 --> 01:03:52,739
They've directly challenged the
sovereign power of the United States.

565
01:03:53,448 --> 01:03:56,076
No more sending messages.

566
01:03:56,243 --> 01:04:00,372
He wants them to get the message
whether the phone rings or not.

567
01:04:00,539 --> 01:04:05,377
- Those are his words?
- Do they sound like his words?

568
01:04:05,544 --> 01:04:10,048
He can't be clear when clarity
is what he wants to avoid.

569
01:04:10,215 --> 01:04:13,760
What he means is the gloves come off.

570
01:04:30,819 --> 01:04:34,406
I'm telling you,
I had nothing to do with it.

571
01:04:34,573 --> 01:04:39,328
I didn't. I wish I had done it,
they deserved it. But it wasn't me.

572
01:04:39,494 --> 01:04:41,621
Who did then?

573
01:04:42,831 --> 01:04:46,626
You know, you have no answers.

574
01:04:48,545 --> 01:04:51,798
Is this the way it was with Castro?
No answers?

575
01:04:51,965 --> 01:04:55,177
- You don't want to hear an answer.
- Yes, I do.

576
01:04:57,638 --> 01:05:01,350
Itwas done to look like you did it.
By one of the others.

577
01:05:01,516 --> 01:05:05,729
As you suspected. It's always
a friend who hates you most.

578
01:05:05,896 --> 01:05:07,981
Give me the phone.

579
01:05:14,780 --> 01:05:17,240
- Rojas.
- Did you do this thing?

580
01:05:17,407 --> 01:05:23,372
Did I do this thing? Are you calling
to ask me if I did this thing?

581
01:05:23,538 --> 01:05:27,459
You don't consult with us.
You put us in danger.

582
01:05:28,710 --> 01:05:32,547
And now you want me
to believe it wasn't you?

583
01:05:32,714 --> 01:05:34,508
It wasn't, Enrique.

584
01:05:34,675 --> 01:05:37,886
The Americans will retaliate
against all of us.

585
01:05:38,053 --> 01:05:41,306
I swear I had
nothing to do with it.

586
01:05:41,473 --> 01:05:45,560
Why do you expect me
to listen to you when you lie?

587
01:05:45,727 --> 01:05:48,271
- Goodbye, Ernesto.
- No, no, no!

588
01:05:48,438 --> 01:05:51,566
Don't hang up.
We must have a meeting.

589
01:05:51,733 --> 01:05:54,611
- When?
- As soon as possible.

590
01:05:57,990 --> 01:06:03,161
Tomorrow night. I am not
telling you, I am asking you!

591
01:06:03,328 --> 01:06:05,163
May we meet tomorrow night?

592
01:06:05,330 --> 01:06:08,375
- Tomorrow afternoon.
- Thank you.

593
01:06:38,488 --> 01:06:40,490
- He's scared.
- He should be.

594
01:06:40,657 --> 01:06:43,618
I don't know what you said to him,
but it was right.

595
01:08:16,586 --> 01:08:18,297
Strange, don't you think?

596
01:08:18,463 --> 01:08:23,218
Jacobs and his secretary
getting killed on the same day.

597
01:08:24,261 --> 01:08:28,682
He wasn't his secretary. He was
a member of the security detail.

598
01:08:28,849 --> 01:08:30,934
Who?

599
01:08:32,185 --> 01:08:36,064
- I don't remember his name.
- I'm talking about Moira.

600
01:08:36,231 --> 01:08:37,524
What?

601
01:08:37,691 --> 01:08:40,027
Moira, remember?
Jacobs's secretary.

602
01:08:40,193 --> 01:08:44,323
I know Moira, honey.
What are you talking about?

603
01:08:49,786 --> 01:08:53,206
- She said he was a Latin Jack Ryan.
- He was.

604
01:08:53,373 --> 01:08:57,544
- That's what she called him.
- The point is, he's Latin.

605
01:08:57,711 --> 01:09:00,047
Which connects her death and Jacobs's

606
01:09:00,213 --> 01:09:03,008
beyond the fact
that they worked together.

607
01:09:03,175 --> 01:09:06,803
You saw somebody you think
is responsible for both killings?

608
01:09:06,970 --> 01:09:08,639
- Yes.
- Yes.

609
01:09:10,474 --> 01:09:12,184
She did.

610
01:09:13,810 --> 01:09:15,312
She did.

611
01:09:22,653 --> 01:09:25,947
I saw him from a distance.
From behind.

612
01:09:26,114 --> 01:09:31,036
- Medium height, medium build, etc?
- Mind if I look at these?

613
01:09:31,203 --> 01:09:33,955
Is that what the people
from the cabin said?

614
01:09:34,122 --> 01:09:35,082
Yeah.

615
01:09:36,792 --> 01:09:41,380
Did you check out
these calls to Venezuela?

616
01:09:42,422 --> 01:09:43,882
Disconnected.

617
01:09:47,219 --> 01:09:49,805
- So you have no leads?
- I have a lot.

618
01:09:49,972 --> 01:09:55,060
Afictitious name on a register. A
stolen phoned-in credit card number.

619
01:09:55,227 --> 01:10:00,440
Two eyewitnesses, one of whom
saw a guy but really didn't see him.

620
01:10:00,607 --> 01:10:03,527
Excuse me,
could you play that again?

621
01:10:03,694 --> 01:10:05,028
Yes, sir.

622
01:10:05,821 --> 01:10:08,031
The machine is still on, Moira.

623
01:10:08,198 --> 01:10:11,243
You have a recording
of the killer's voice.

624
01:10:12,327 --> 01:10:14,496
Maybe.

625
01:10:17,374 --> 01:10:22,713
Jack. I think we've got something.
This is from the answering machine.

626
01:10:22,879 --> 01:10:27,426
And this was recorded yesterday.
I'll play it for you.

627
01:10:31,722 --> 01:10:34,599
The machine is still on, Moira.

628
01:10:35,767 --> 01:10:37,144
And...

629
01:10:37,311 --> 01:10:41,940
He's scared. I don't know what
you said to him, but it was right.

630
01:10:42,107 --> 01:10:45,193
Run a match on that.

631
01:10:47,904 --> 01:10:50,449
He's Cuban.

632
01:10:50,615 --> 01:10:53,869
35 to 45.

633
01:10:54,036 --> 01:10:58,623
Educated in the United States.
Eastern United States.

634
01:10:59,666 --> 01:11:02,336
- It's the same voice.
- You're sure?

635
01:11:02,502 --> 01:11:04,796
- Yeah.
- How sure?

636
01:11:10,218 --> 01:11:11,803
90 percent.

637
01:11:13,013 --> 01:11:16,224
- I need a name.
- Could be hundreds of thousands...

638
01:11:16,391 --> 01:11:20,103
I know. I need a name,
and I need it quick.

639
01:11:38,330 --> 01:11:41,333
300 is topside.

640
01:12:25,252 --> 01:12:27,629
Target is set.

641
01:12:29,840 --> 01:12:32,551
- Hector!
- Enrique!

642
01:12:33,969 --> 01:12:36,263
Good to see you!

643
01:12:36,430 --> 01:12:39,099
- It was not easy for us.
- How are you?

644
01:12:39,599 --> 01:12:43,603
Rojas, Diaz...

645
01:12:46,398 --> 01:12:48,442
What the hell is this?

646
01:12:48,608 --> 01:12:51,278
What the hell is this?

647
01:12:53,322 --> 01:12:55,782
My new toy. Like it?

648
01:12:56,867 --> 01:12:58,827
You see this?

649
01:12:58,994 --> 01:13:03,957
That's your new target,
unless it's not big enough.

650
01:13:09,004 --> 01:13:12,424
Variable, this is Easy Rhino.
Do you copy? Over.

651
01:13:13,258 --> 01:13:15,510
Loud and clear, Easy Rhino.

652
01:13:15,677 --> 01:13:19,681
- Do we have a gig?
- That's a Rog.

653
01:13:25,520 --> 01:13:28,398
Target is lit.

654
01:13:28,565 --> 01:13:30,359
Start the music.

655
01:13:31,485 --> 01:13:33,320
Into attack.

656
01:13:34,404 --> 01:13:39,534
Pickle's hot. Target is acquired
and lit. Coming down.

657
01:13:44,122 --> 01:13:51,046
Fernandez, Vega...
Looks like a full house.

658
01:13:59,972 --> 01:14:03,016
Damn it!
Why doesn't he fix this road?

659
01:14:03,976 --> 01:14:07,354
Shit! Thought we had everybody.

660
01:14:08,188 --> 01:14:10,482
Keep the target painted.

661
01:14:39,136 --> 01:14:40,762
Sir?

662
01:14:46,059 --> 01:14:47,102
Boom.

663
01:14:56,486 --> 01:14:58,030
Mother of God!

664
01:15:02,701 --> 01:15:04,870
Circular error probability zero.

665
01:15:05,037 --> 01:15:09,708
Impact with high-order detonation.
Have a nice day.

666
01:15:15,255 --> 01:15:18,592
The man's completely out of control.
He has no...

667
01:15:27,768 --> 01:15:31,229
His name is Cortez, Felix Cortez.

668
01:15:31,396 --> 01:15:33,774
A colonel
in Cuba's intelligence service

669
01:15:33,940 --> 01:15:36,026
until a few years ago. Disappeared.

670
01:15:36,234 --> 01:15:41,114
Turned up working for the Macheteros,
a terrorist group in Puerto Rico.

671
01:15:41,281 --> 01:15:42,699
Disappeared again.

672
01:15:42,866 --> 01:15:47,287
Yesterday, we taped him
talking to a Cali cartel subject.

673
01:15:47,454 --> 01:15:52,000
I'll fax what I have on him.
If he shows, pick him up, OK?

674
01:15:52,167 --> 01:15:56,046
- You know I can't do that.
- I mean the police, the Colombians.

675
01:15:56,213 --> 01:16:00,300
The Colombian police
do not pick up members of the cartel.

676
01:16:00,467 --> 01:16:04,221
Unless they've got a death wish.
You've been down here.

677
01:16:05,389 --> 01:16:07,099
Wait a minute.

678
01:16:07,265 --> 01:16:12,270
Oh, Jesus!
Jack, something's happened here.

679
01:16:24,157 --> 01:16:28,704
At least 30 people were killed,
including women and children.

680
01:16:28,870 --> 01:16:33,333
The bomb exploded in a car
belongingto a Rojas associate.

681
01:16:33,500 --> 01:16:37,296
- Jack?
- Yeah, are you watching this?

682
01:16:37,462 --> 01:16:40,674
- Did this just happen?
- Just now.

683
01:16:43,802 --> 01:16:48,056
Send me all the stuff, and we'll
put a tail on him if we spot him.

684
01:16:48,223 --> 01:16:51,518
If he's still alive. I've got to go.

685
01:16:51,685 --> 01:16:55,856
...a series of explosions.
- Cops claim the violence...

686
01:16:56,023 --> 01:16:59,484
- A surgical strike, you said.
- It was perfect.

687
01:16:59,651 --> 01:17:03,739
- They brought out a kid. On NBC.
- Take the gloves off, you said.

688
01:17:03,905 --> 01:17:07,534
- I know what I said.
- A bit late to change your mind.

689
01:17:07,701 --> 01:17:10,078
I'm not changing my mind.

690
01:17:10,245 --> 01:17:14,624
I hadn't counted on
this kind of collateral damage.

691
01:17:16,043 --> 01:17:19,046
- Neither had he.
- It will be interpreted as I said.

692
01:17:19,212 --> 01:17:23,300
Rivalry that ended
in the blast of a car bomb.

693
01:17:23,467 --> 01:17:24,509
Goodnight.

694
01:17:39,691 --> 01:17:43,070
- Morning, Rose. Finish the report?
- Hot off the press.

695
01:17:43,236 --> 01:17:44,655
Thanks.

696
01:17:47,240 --> 01:17:50,911
Could any of the bombing victims'
names be aliases?

697
01:17:51,078 --> 01:17:55,791
No. All IDs have been confirmed.
Who were you hoping for?

698
01:17:55,957 --> 01:17:59,836
If he's not here, he's not here.
Cortez. He's not here.

699
01:18:02,089 --> 01:18:06,301
- Why was Operations copied on this?
- Ritter requested it.

700
01:18:07,386 --> 01:18:10,472
Ritter? You look very nice today.

701
01:18:11,431 --> 01:18:13,517
Thank you.

702
01:18:27,072 --> 01:18:28,782
Car bomb.

703
01:18:38,417 --> 01:18:41,044
What happens
when a car bomb goes off?

704
01:18:41,211 --> 01:18:45,173
- It explodes.
- It blows up and out?

705
01:18:45,340 --> 01:18:47,843
And a missile?

706
01:18:50,929 --> 01:18:53,724
- This deeper crater?
- That's characteristic.

707
01:18:53,890 --> 01:18:56,143
Bring up the satellite photo.

708
01:19:02,441 --> 01:19:05,694
HMX and TNT.

709
01:19:05,861 --> 01:19:09,531
When you mix it 70-30,
you get a compound called Octol.

710
01:19:09,698 --> 01:19:12,993
Put enough explosives in a car,
you get a crater that big.

711
01:19:13,160 --> 01:19:17,456
- It's very stable. Very expensive.
- Would it still be in the crater?

712
01:19:17,622 --> 01:19:21,209
- Very violent.
- There would be pieces all around.

713
01:19:21,793 --> 01:19:28,634
- Where is Octol made?
- Lots of places. Europe. The US.

714
01:19:28,800 --> 01:19:33,639
But nobody uses it. Nobody can
afford it except the military.

715
01:19:33,805 --> 01:19:39,061
An aerial bomb would do that.
But that's not an aerial bomb.

716
01:19:39,227 --> 01:19:40,604
- It's not?
- No.

717
01:19:40,771 --> 01:19:44,399
There is also
a cellulose residue on everything.

718
01:19:44,566 --> 01:19:47,736
There should be shrapnel.
Here and here.

719
01:19:47,903 --> 01:19:51,657
- But there isn't.
- No bomb fragments.

720
01:20:35,325 --> 01:20:39,830
"Cellulose encased
laser-guided bomb."

721
01:20:41,915 --> 01:20:43,583
Paper.

722
01:20:48,005 --> 01:20:49,589
The Americans are here.

