01:21:20,287 --> 01:21:24,791
"We have something in common.
We cannot implement policy

724
01:21:24,958 --> 01:21:28,920
without tacit authorisation
from our employer."

725
01:21:29,087 --> 01:21:34,051
"We also both know that there are
American troops in Colombia

726
01:21:34,217 --> 01:21:37,179
fighting an illegal war."

727
01:21:38,221 --> 01:21:43,143
"I will be at Hotel Paloma de Oro
in Panama City on Wednesday."

728
01:21:43,310 --> 01:21:45,228
"I suggest we meet."

729
01:22:37,531 --> 01:22:41,618
- Six, this is Point. Over.
- Six here.

730
01:22:42,953 --> 01:22:45,247
The stuffs here, a lot of it.

731
01:22:45,414 --> 01:22:50,335
I'm also looking
at 100 to 150 men, armed,

732
01:22:50,502 --> 01:22:53,380
waiting around for something. Over.

733
01:22:53,547 --> 01:22:56,133
Colombian Army? Over.

734
01:22:59,511 --> 01:23:02,014
Negative.
They look like mercenaries.

735
01:23:02,180 --> 01:23:05,767
- Over.
- Alright. Get back here.

736
01:23:05,934 --> 01:23:09,980
Abort mission.
I say again, abort mission. Out.

737
01:23:11,231 --> 01:23:14,192
150 armed men?

738
01:23:34,921 --> 01:23:36,882
Raise your arms, please.

739
01:23:52,481 --> 01:23:57,277
Thank you for responding to my note.
And so promptly.

740
01:23:57,444 --> 01:24:01,323
I had nothing to do
with the death of Mr Jacobs.

741
01:24:01,490 --> 01:24:06,078
It was an act of madness.
But typical of the men I work for.

742
01:24:07,704 --> 01:24:11,750
- What do you want?
- Same as you. Mineral water.

743
01:24:12,626 --> 01:24:17,506
You agree that as long as Americans
want drugs, someone will supply them?

744
01:24:17,673 --> 01:24:20,676
I don't want to be here
any longer than I have to.

745
01:24:20,842 --> 01:24:24,137
You mentioned a gang war.
What does that mean?

746
01:24:24,304 --> 01:24:28,850
- That we want the same thing.
- Same thing? Really?

747
01:24:29,017 --> 01:24:31,603
Only, so far,
you've done all the work.

748
01:24:31,770 --> 01:24:34,022
You took care of the little fish.

749
01:24:34,189 --> 01:24:36,900
I will take care of
the one that got away.

750
01:24:37,067 --> 01:24:41,863
Once Escobedo is gone,
I will be in a position to help you.

751
01:24:42,030 --> 01:24:46,284
- You want to help me?
- Your country. Your people.

752
01:24:46,451 --> 01:24:48,996
By restructuring the drug trade.

753
01:24:49,162 --> 01:24:53,208
By regulating it. What would you say

754
01:24:53,375 --> 01:24:58,171
if I promised to halve the cocaine
shipments to the US?

755
01:24:59,631 --> 01:25:03,760
I'd say you'd been using
too much of your product.

756
01:25:03,927 --> 01:25:07,764
I can also promise you
regular quotas on major arrests

757
01:25:07,931 --> 01:25:11,018
that your police
can take credit for.

758
01:25:11,184 --> 01:25:14,896
Imagine. Dramatic seizures.
Drastic reductions.

759
01:25:15,063 --> 01:25:19,985
No more senseless violence.
You'll have your victory.

760
01:25:24,156 --> 01:25:25,991
In return for what?

761
01:25:27,242 --> 01:25:30,996
I also need a victory,
to establish my position

762
01:25:31,163 --> 01:25:36,043
with what is left of the cartel,
so I can help you.

763
01:25:36,585 --> 01:25:41,465
I need to defeat those soldiers
blowing up everything they see.

764
01:25:41,632 --> 01:25:47,804
Give me maps of their locations.
Cut off their communications.

765
01:25:54,353 --> 01:26:00,317
DEA's sending the audio surveillance
tape. They haven't got it yet.

766
01:26:02,861 --> 01:26:07,824
You know what you think about
when you're lying here?

767
01:26:09,618 --> 01:26:13,455
You know you're gonna die,
and you think...

768
01:26:14,790 --> 01:26:18,919
...that's alright.
You lived a long time.

769
01:26:19,544 --> 01:26:21,713
You had a family that loved you.

770
01:26:21,880 --> 01:26:26,551
You had a job that you thought
made a difference.

771
01:26:27,177 --> 01:26:30,263
That you thought was honourable.

772
01:26:31,139 --> 01:26:33,892
And then you see this.

773
01:26:37,896 --> 01:26:40,899
I'm afraid if I dig any deeper...

774
01:26:42,025 --> 01:26:45,278
...no one's gonna like what I find.

775
01:26:50,283 --> 01:26:52,369
You took an oath...

776
01:26:53,829 --> 01:26:56,623
...if you recall...

777
01:26:58,959 --> 01:27:02,379
...when you first came
to work for me.

778
01:27:02,546 --> 01:27:08,385
And I don't mean to the National
Security Advisor of the US.

779
01:27:09,303 --> 01:27:11,763
I mean to his boss.

780
01:27:12,764 --> 01:27:15,642
And I don't mean the President.

781
01:27:17,102 --> 01:27:20,605
You gave your word to...

782
01:27:21,982 --> 01:27:24,276
...his boss.

783
01:27:24,443 --> 01:27:26,361
You gave your word...

784
01:27:27,446 --> 01:27:32,075
...to the people
of the United States.

785
01:27:33,160 --> 01:27:36,079
Your word is who you are.

786
01:27:41,251 --> 01:27:44,171
What else have you got there?

787
01:27:49,134 --> 01:27:52,137
I brought you some new magazines.

788
01:28:01,521 --> 01:28:05,776
The situation in East Timor seems
to have stabilised during the day.

789
01:28:05,942 --> 01:28:07,444
Good.

790
01:28:07,611 --> 01:28:11,823
- Is that it?
- Except for the other thing.

791
01:28:12,282 --> 01:28:15,577
We've accomplished a lot.
We're seeing results.

792
01:28:15,744 --> 01:28:19,831
Drug shipments are down.
Price on the street is rising.

793
01:28:19,998 --> 01:28:24,628
The perception is the administration
is doing something right.

794
01:28:24,795 --> 01:28:27,422
What's the bad news?

795
01:28:29,508 --> 01:28:35,222
I'm worried about the car bomb coming
so soon after Jacobs's assassination.

796
01:28:36,765 --> 01:28:39,810
Just the kind of thing
reporters live for.

797
01:28:39,977 --> 01:28:44,106
- They'd love to make a connection.
- And you think they will?

798
01:28:45,357 --> 01:28:49,486
I think it's time
the whole thing went away.

799
01:28:49,653 --> 01:28:53,281
- If that's what you think.
- I think so.

800
01:28:55,117 --> 01:28:59,871
Then it should go away.
It never happened.

801
01:29:04,584 --> 01:29:08,380
Well, it's possible.

802
01:29:08,547 --> 01:29:13,802
It would be easier if you told me
whose system you want to break into.

803
01:29:13,969 --> 01:29:15,971
- Morning, Dr Ryan.
- Morning.

804
01:29:35,240 --> 01:29:39,411
Well, we're way beyond birthdays now.

805
01:29:41,079 --> 01:29:45,751
I'm gonna have to write
a special program here.

806
01:29:48,128 --> 01:29:49,963
Right.

807
01:29:56,470 --> 01:29:59,931
OK, sweetheart, let's get to work.

808
01:30:01,391 --> 01:30:03,477
Fine, good.

809
01:30:04,519 --> 01:30:07,689
Yes. Here we go.

810
01:30:44,601 --> 01:30:46,311
Jesus!

811
01:31:05,580 --> 01:31:08,792
Reciprocity. What's that?

812
01:31:20,887 --> 01:31:22,681
- Yeah?
- I forgot to tell you,

813
01:31:22,848 --> 01:31:24,349
after you get the code,

814
01:31:24,516 --> 01:31:28,061
wait until he's off his system
before you log on.

815
01:31:28,228 --> 01:31:31,982
- He will know it when you do.
- Jesus, Petey, it's too late.

816
01:31:32,149 --> 01:31:34,693
Oh, my God!

817
01:32:05,223 --> 01:32:07,225
Cutter.

818
01:32:20,822 --> 01:32:21,907
Yeah?

819
01:32:22,074 --> 01:32:25,911
- Bob, Jack Ryan here.
- Good morning, Jack.

820
01:32:26,078 --> 01:32:30,415
Listen, maybe we got off
to a bad start.

821
01:32:30,582 --> 01:32:35,671
We're going to work together.
We should get to know each other.

822
01:32:35,837 --> 01:32:40,133
Do you play tennis?
Tennis? Do you play tennis?

823
01:32:40,300 --> 01:32:44,638
- Yeah, I play tennis.
- How about we get together?

824
01:32:44,805 --> 01:32:48,100
Next week?
Hour before we startwork?

825
01:32:55,399 --> 01:32:57,401
- Jack?
- Yeah.

826
01:32:58,110 --> 01:33:01,780
Computer theft is a serious crime.

827
01:33:05,659 --> 01:33:09,121
So are crimes
against the Constitution.

828
01:33:10,622 --> 01:33:12,708
Son of a bitch!

829
01:33:24,761 --> 01:33:26,638
Son of a bitch!

830
01:33:31,059 --> 01:33:33,145
Come on, come on.

831
01:33:35,564 --> 01:33:37,649
Clark.

832
01:33:49,703 --> 01:33:51,204
Yeah.

833
01:34:13,393 --> 01:34:16,563
You'll go to jail, pal.

834
01:34:16,730 --> 01:34:20,275
What is that? What do you think
you have there?

835
01:34:20,442 --> 01:34:22,110
You broke the law.

836
01:34:23,153 --> 01:34:27,240
You are such a Boy Scout.

837
01:34:27,407 --> 01:34:30,786
Look at you. You see everything
in black and white.

838
01:34:30,953 --> 01:34:34,915
No, not black and white, Ritter.
Right and wrong!

839
01:34:35,082 --> 01:34:39,336
- You see? There you go again.
- Why was I kept out of it?

840
01:34:39,503 --> 01:34:43,131
You're neck deep in it.
You went before Congress.

841
01:34:43,298 --> 01:34:46,301
You got the money for it.
You lied under oath...

842
01:34:46,468 --> 01:34:50,931
- I never lied to Congress!
- You told them no troops.

843
01:34:51,098 --> 01:34:54,685
- There are troops!
- You know I didn't know that.

844
01:34:54,851 --> 01:35:00,524
No. I have no recollection of that.
That's the term you have to learn.

845
01:35:00,691 --> 01:35:04,653
- Who authorised this?
- Sure, they'll ask you that.

846
01:35:04,820 --> 01:35:09,700
- Who authorised this?
- I have no recollection, Senator.

847
01:35:14,621 --> 01:35:19,084
I did not sign up for somebody's
bullshit political agenda.

848
01:35:19,251 --> 01:35:23,171
Who authorised this? Cutter?

849
01:35:23,338 --> 01:35:27,009
Cutter couldn't tie his shoes
without permission.

850
01:35:31,305 --> 01:35:34,683
- If I go down, you're going with me.
- Wrong again.

851
01:35:34,850 --> 01:35:39,062
I have an autographed
"Get Out of Jail Free" card.

852
01:35:40,314 --> 01:35:44,901
"The President authorises the Deputy
Director CIA, Robert Ritter,

853
01:35:45,068 --> 01:35:50,449
to conduct Operation Reciprocity
including all support necessary."

854
01:35:50,615 --> 01:35:55,412
"This operation is deemed important
to the national security of the US."

855
01:35:55,579 --> 01:35:57,247
Etc, etc, etc.

856
01:35:59,124 --> 01:36:03,795
You don't have one of these,
do you, Jack?

857
01:36:12,763 --> 01:36:17,643
Grey! The world is grey, Jack.

858
01:36:50,217 --> 01:36:55,305
Got any idea how I'm gonna
get out of this mess?

859
01:36:55,472 --> 01:36:58,266
Absolutely none.

860
01:37:07,192 --> 01:37:10,779
Yeah. This is he.

861
01:37:14,950 --> 01:37:17,327
When?

862
01:37:21,498 --> 01:37:23,583
James?

863
01:37:25,252 --> 01:37:27,170
Thank you.

864
01:37:27,504 --> 01:37:35,178
Admiral James Greer devoted his life
to his country and his family,

865
01:37:35,345 --> 01:37:39,641
giving selflessly
of both his wisdom and his love.

866
01:37:40,851 --> 01:37:44,563
He served his country
for more than 50 years.

867
01:37:44,730 --> 01:37:49,901
Enlisting in the Navy at 17.
Graduating from the Academy.

868
01:37:50,068 --> 01:37:53,697
Achieving three stars for his flag.

869
01:37:53,864 --> 01:37:57,743
He lived through tumultuous events
in his country's life.

870
01:37:57,909 --> 01:38:02,039
He participated in them. He made
them clearer to the rest of us,

871
01:38:02,205 --> 01:38:08,462
with his knowledge, his honesty,
his integrity and his courage.

872
01:38:17,888 --> 01:38:20,390
I can't see them,
but I know they're there.

873
01:38:20,557 --> 01:38:24,186
Five kilometres due east
from your position.

874
01:38:28,774 --> 01:38:32,110
Keep pushing forward.
We'll trap them.

875
01:38:32,277 --> 01:38:35,781
Never, though, was he deluded
into thinking that one man

876
01:38:35,947 --> 01:38:38,867
could solve the ills of the world.

877
01:38:39,493 --> 01:38:43,664
Always the soldier, on the
battlefields of the South Pacific,

878
01:38:43,830 --> 01:38:48,919
Korea, Vietnam and Washington,
he fought as part of a unit

879
01:38:49,086 --> 01:38:51,421
to preserve the ideals...

880
01:38:51,588 --> 01:38:55,050
- Knife, this is Variable, over.
...of his nation.

881
01:38:55,217 --> 01:38:57,678
Knife! This is Variable, over.

882
01:38:59,054 --> 01:39:03,266
To the refuge of the earth,
we entrust our friend's body.

883
01:39:03,433 --> 01:39:08,188
To the protection of our God
in Heaven, we entrust his soul.

884
01:39:08,355 --> 01:39:12,693
To ourselves, we entrust his spirit

885
01:39:12,859 --> 01:39:15,946
and the principles he lived by.

886
01:39:16,947 --> 01:39:18,949
We're gonna miss you, James.

887
01:39:41,638 --> 01:39:44,599
Variable, this is Knife, over.

888
01:39:44,766 --> 01:39:47,769
Variable, this is Knife, over.

889
01:39:47,936 --> 01:39:51,440
Variable, I am not receiving.
We are under heavy attack.

890
01:39:51,606 --> 01:39:54,985
- Need air support, over.
- Go, go, go!

891
01:40:16,173 --> 01:40:20,010
Variable, this is Knife, over!
Switch!

892
01:40:52,376 --> 01:40:56,380
Variable, this is Knife!
Where the hell are you?

893
01:41:11,478 --> 01:41:15,107
Present arms.

894
01:41:17,943 --> 01:41:22,447
On behalf of a grateful nation,
our condolences.

895
01:41:22,614 --> 01:41:26,368
- He was a very great patriot.
- Thank you.

896
01:41:34,876 --> 01:41:37,004
All aim.

897
01:42:04,364 --> 01:42:06,908
- Hello?
- Jean Fowler for Dr Jack Ryan.

898
01:42:07,075 --> 01:42:08,785
This is he.

899
01:42:08,952 --> 01:42:12,331
Jack? You've got to hear this.

900
01:42:12,497 --> 01:42:15,083
Picked it up this morning.

901
01:42:15,250 --> 01:42:21,173
Variable, this is Knife. We are
under attack, need air support.

902
01:42:21,340 --> 01:42:24,635
Variable, this is Knife,
where the hell are you?

903
01:42:25,427 --> 01:42:28,347
Jack, what do you want me
to do with this?

904
01:42:29,431 --> 01:42:33,810
Make a copy, Jean.
Make ten copies.

905
01:42:33,977 --> 01:42:37,064
Get them to me
as quick as you can. Thanks.

906
01:42:39,566 --> 01:42:44,738
Jesus. They're going to leave
those guys down there.

907
01:43:27,322 --> 01:43:33,412
He's on American 915.
He'll be in Bogota 7:50pm.

908
01:43:45,340 --> 01:43:47,342
- Yeah?
- It's Ritter.

909
01:43:47,509 --> 01:43:51,221
- Where the fuck have you been?
- We have a problem.

910
01:43:51,388 --> 01:43:54,308
We've got a disaster!
I can't get through to my men.

911
01:43:55,017 --> 01:43:58,520
We had to shut down
the satellite link.

912
01:43:59,938 --> 01:44:02,941
- Clark?
- You had to what?

913
01:44:04,276 --> 01:44:10,198
It's Ryan. He found out everything.
He threatened to walk up the Hill

914
01:44:10,365 --> 01:44:13,285
if we didn't
shut down the operation.

915
01:44:13,452 --> 01:44:19,207
OK. It's shut down. Just give me
some air and my men are out of there.

916
01:44:20,667 --> 01:44:26,923
Clark, maybe you're not hearing me.
There is no air. We are shut down.

917
01:44:28,675 --> 01:44:32,095
I'm on a plane.
I'm gonna kill him.

918
01:44:33,472 --> 01:44:35,557
Ritter?

919
01:44:37,309 --> 01:44:39,853
Don't get on a plane.
He's coming to you.

920
01:44:40,020 --> 01:44:44,024
American Airlines at 1950 hours
with no security.

921
01:44:44,191 --> 01:44:48,445
- Who is this?
- National Security Advisor Cutter.

922
01:44:48,612 --> 01:44:51,615
Once Ryan's gone, we're back on line.

923
01:44:52,199 --> 01:44:54,284
You understand?

924
01:44:55,410 --> 01:44:57,746
Yes, sir.

925
01:46:18,160 --> 01:46:19,786
Clark.

926
01:46:19,953 --> 01:46:21,788
- Jesus!
- Get in the van.

927
01:46:21,955 --> 01:46:24,291
Don't be an asshole,
I came to find you.

928
01:46:24,458 --> 01:46:26,793
You found me. Get in.

929
01:46:28,086 --> 01:46:29,588
Alright.

930
01:46:30,922 --> 01:46:32,633
Behind the wheel.

931
01:46:34,134 --> 01:46:36,094
Clark.

932
01:46:37,012 --> 01:46:39,514
Drive.

933
01:47:06,708 --> 01:47:09,336
- Ritter.
- Ryan's dead.

934
01:47:11,254 --> 01:47:12,464
How?

935
01:47:13,674 --> 01:47:16,843
I killed him. Turn the op back on.

936
01:47:20,013 --> 01:47:25,143
You said get rid of Ryan
and we're back in business, right?

937
01:47:50,168 --> 01:47:52,337
What the hell are you doing here?

938
01:47:54,715 --> 01:47:57,926
I came to help you
get those guys out.

939
01:47:59,469 --> 01:48:02,180
What can you do to help me?

940
01:48:07,728 --> 01:48:10,605
What do you need?

941
01:48:10,772 --> 01:48:12,357
A helicopter.

942
01:48:14,735 --> 01:48:17,529
A helicopter.

943
01:48:25,579 --> 01:48:26,955
No, thank you.

944
01:48:29,958 --> 01:48:33,170
- Is this happy hour?
- It's always happy hour.

945
01:48:33,337 --> 01:48:37,132
- Your pilot owns thisjoint?
- He lives here.

946
01:48:42,638 --> 01:48:44,097
Here he is.

947
01:48:55,192 --> 01:48:57,110
- Morning.
- Morning.

948
01:48:57,277 --> 01:49:00,113
Morning. I'm here to rent the Huey.

949
01:49:00,280 --> 01:49:04,868
Sorry, we don't rent it any more.
But it is for sale.

950
01:49:05,911 --> 01:49:07,955
How much is it?

951
01:49:09,247 --> 01:49:11,917
Two million dollars.

952
01:49:16,421 --> 01:49:20,008
My pilot and I would
have to do a test flight.

953
01:49:20,175 --> 01:49:23,387
Of course.
You just have to leave a deposit.

954
01:49:25,055 --> 01:49:26,974
How much is that?

955
01:49:27,140 --> 01:49:28,767
Two million dollars.

956
01:49:34,439 --> 01:49:37,776
Would you take a company cheque?

957
01:49:44,283 --> 01:49:45,909
Yes.

958
01:49:53,709 --> 01:49:58,005
- Here we go.
- Big son of a bitch, ain't she?

959
01:49:59,631 --> 01:50:04,094
- Do you have any time in this type?
- Nine o'clock.

960
01:50:13,979 --> 01:50:19,943
- Get out of my chopper.
- No. Mychopper. Let's go.

961
01:50:40,714 --> 01:50:43,925
Their last communication
put them here.

962
01:50:45,135 --> 01:50:50,265
The closest extraction point is here,
in this gorge.

963
01:50:51,266 --> 01:50:52,893
I got it.

964
01:51:12,496 --> 01:51:16,208
- Is that a body down there?
- Yeah.

965
01:51:18,085 --> 01:51:21,797
- One of ours?
- One of mine.

966
01:51:25,175 --> 01:51:29,972
Find a place to set her down.
We'll look for the others.

967
01:52:13,140 --> 01:52:17,853
Nowhere to run to.
No place to hide.

968
01:52:18,020 --> 01:52:23,275
Blood trails everywhere.
They all lead to the river.

969
01:52:36,496 --> 01:52:40,626
These are the falls
we saw from the air.

970
01:52:40,792 --> 01:52:44,546
The bodies should be
about 50 metres down.

971
01:52:56,350 --> 01:53:01,438
You left us!
You left us with no support at all!

972
01:53:01,605 --> 01:53:03,899
Fuck, you left us out to dry!

973
01:53:04,066 --> 01:53:06,151
- You son of a bitch!
- Easy! Easy!

974
01:53:09,112 --> 01:53:12,407
- It's not his fault.
- Whose fault is it?

975
01:53:14,284 --> 01:53:16,662
It's my fault.

976
01:53:20,958 --> 01:53:23,543
It's my fault.

977
01:53:35,222 --> 01:53:39,309
I was on point
when the last attack came.

978
01:53:40,352 --> 01:53:42,688
Over a mile away.

979
01:53:43,772 --> 01:53:46,066
By the time I got back, it was over.

980
01:53:47,526 --> 01:53:50,737
They were taking the Captain and Oso.

981
01:53:51,530 --> 01:53:52,906
The others?

982
01:53:54,616 --> 01:53:56,368
I buried them.

983
01:54:05,210 --> 01:54:07,379
Road to the town.

984
01:54:07,546 --> 01:54:10,882
They loaded the prisoners here.
Blood everywhere.

985
01:54:11,049 --> 01:54:14,845
- God knows where they are now.
- Escobedo knows.

986
01:54:15,012 --> 01:54:18,307
What are you going to do?
Knock on his door?

987
01:54:24,938 --> 01:54:29,985
Morning. I'd like to see Ernesto
Escobedo. I have no appointment.

988
01:54:31,403 --> 01:54:33,614
Gracias.

989
01:54:43,457 --> 01:54:45,626
OK.

990
01:54:47,419 --> 01:54:49,379
Hands up.

991
01:54:50,005 --> 01:54:51,965
Hands up!

992
01:54:53,508 --> 01:54:55,844
Wallet.

993
01:55:00,223 --> 01:55:03,018
It's a tape recorder.

994
01:55:06,563 --> 01:55:09,149
He's in.

995
01:55:11,693 --> 01:55:14,696
Bird, this is Variable, over.

996
01:55:16,615 --> 01:55:20,535
Bird, this is Variable, over.

997
01:55:36,468 --> 01:55:40,389
Dr Ryan. Come in.

998
01:55:54,027 --> 01:55:58,115
Sit down. What can I do for you?

999
01:55:59,366 --> 01:56:05,080
I didn't know who else to turn to.
I have a problem.

1000
01:56:06,290 --> 01:56:10,002
An associate of mine,
a coffee buyer and his assistant,

1001
01:56:10,168 --> 01:56:13,088
were on a business trip
in this area.

1002
01:56:13,255 --> 01:56:17,050
They unexpectedly disappeared
yesterday. I'm very concerned.

1003
01:56:17,217 --> 01:56:19,428
Coffee buyer?

1004
01:56:19,594 --> 01:56:22,347
It's very important to me
to find them.

1005
01:56:22,514 --> 01:56:25,767
Coffee buying is becoming
a dangerous business.

1006
01:56:26,935 --> 01:56:31,732
Yes. Well, it was for Peter Hardin.

1007
01:56:34,693 --> 01:56:38,238
- Who?
- He was a client of Lindo Coffee.

1008
01:56:38,405 --> 01:56:43,201
- Lindo Coffee has many clients.
- You must have heard of this one.

1009
01:56:43,368 --> 01:56:47,205
He owed your company
a great deal of money.

1010
01:56:47,372 --> 01:56:51,376
Well, I'll have to talk to accounting
about that.

1011
01:56:52,753 --> 01:56:55,255
$650 million.

1012
01:56:58,342 --> 01:57:00,594
And change.

1013
01:57:01,970 --> 01:57:07,059
Are you offering to help me with
the collection of an unpaid debt?

1014
01:57:07,225 --> 01:57:10,354
- No.
- What are you offering?

1015
01:57:11,647 --> 01:57:16,318
Atrade.
Felix Cortez has sold you out.

1016
01:57:16,485 --> 01:57:19,112
His next move is to murder you,
your family,

1017
01:57:19,279 --> 01:57:20,948
and take over the cartel.

1018
01:57:21,114 --> 01:57:23,075
Where's my tape recorder?

1019
01:57:29,539 --> 01:57:31,500
Play the tape.

1020
01:58:05,200 --> 01:58:07,494
Let's move.

1021
01:58:36,940 --> 01:58:40,319
I'd like you to meet
my new friend, Dr Ryan.

1022
01:58:40,485 --> 01:58:43,780
Doctor? Why? Is somebody sick?

1023
01:58:57,169 --> 01:58:58,879
What does he want?

1024
01:59:00,922 --> 01:59:04,384
The safe return of his associates.

1025
01:59:04,551 --> 01:59:08,805
And what does he offer us in return?

1026
01:59:08,972 --> 01:59:11,475
You.

1027
01:59:17,147 --> 01:59:21,526
Whatever this man has told you
is a lie. He lies for a living.

1028
01:59:21,693 --> 01:59:26,323
He's in the intelligence business.
You're in the intelligence business!

1029
01:59:32,704 --> 01:59:35,666
You've taken care of the little fish.

1030
01:59:35,832 --> 01:59:38,543
I will take care
of the one that got away.

1031
01:59:38,710 --> 01:59:43,423
Once Escobedo is gone,
I will be in a position to help you.

1032
01:59:43,590 --> 01:59:47,803
So, the question is...

1033
01:59:49,137 --> 01:59:51,640
...what am I supposed to do with you?

1034
01:59:54,726 --> 01:59:57,771
Well? I guess I'm supposed
to kill you with this bat!

1035
02:00:06,280 --> 02:00:08,699
Get up.

1036
02:00:13,245 --> 02:00:17,582
Dramatic seizures. Drastic
reductions, no more violence...

1037
02:00:17,749 --> 02:00:21,128
You'll have your victory.

1038
02:00:21,795 --> 02:00:23,505
In return for what?

1039
02:01:03,712 --> 02:01:05,797
- Where are they?
- They're here.

1040
02:01:07,716 --> 02:01:12,763
Kill the plant. The American
killed Ernesto! Let's go!

1041
02:02:00,519 --> 02:02:02,938
Bird to Variable, over.

1042
02:02:16,034 --> 02:02:17,619
Bird, this is Variable.

1043
02:02:17,786 --> 02:02:20,122
Where the hell are you?

1044
02:02:20,289 --> 02:02:25,043
I'm cruising about five clicks
south of the village.

1045
02:02:25,961 --> 02:02:30,048
- Stay there. I'll get back to you.
- Roger that.

1046
02:02:41,893 --> 02:02:44,730
- No one.
- The prisoners!

1047
02:03:31,234 --> 02:03:34,529
Come on, guys. Let's go, son.

1048
02:03:35,530 --> 02:03:38,325
We're going home, boys.

1049
02:04:51,315 --> 02:04:54,067
Pick us up
at the Lindo Coffee factory.

1050
02:06:30,497 --> 02:06:34,459
Not only can I expose you
to the press, so can the soldiers.

1051
02:06:34,626 --> 02:06:41,341
Do you want to take your chances
with the courts and the reporters?

1052
02:06:41,508 --> 02:06:46,179
Do you want to end the career
of your commander in chief?

1053
02:07:30,182 --> 02:07:32,517
Let's go!

1054
02:07:59,586 --> 02:08:03,090
Get your asses in here!
Come on, we got to go!

1055
02:08:06,093 --> 02:08:08,345
Come on!

1056
02:08:15,018 --> 02:08:17,354
Hold it! We wait for Ryan!

1057
02:08:17,521 --> 02:08:19,564
Yeah? We're out of here!

1058
02:08:26,822 --> 02:08:29,950
Set it down! He's down there!

1059
02:08:42,045 --> 02:08:43,714
Come on!

1060
02:09:03,025 --> 02:09:04,860
I've got you!

1061
02:09:11,742 --> 02:09:14,286
Chavez, cover me!

1062
02:09:23,128 --> 02:09:26,506
Your hand. Give me your hand!

1063
02:10:32,030 --> 02:10:35,158
The President will see you now, sir.

1064
02:10:47,421 --> 02:10:50,757
Jack! I'm glad you're here.

1065
02:10:51,925 --> 02:10:56,054
Sit down.
Can I get you anything?

1066
02:10:56,221 --> 02:10:58,557
No.

1067
02:10:58,724 --> 02:11:03,020
- Come on, sit down.
- I would prefer to stand, sir.

1068
02:11:05,105 --> 02:11:11,612
Some things have gone on here
that I'm just becoming aware of.

1069
02:11:11,778 --> 02:11:16,033
I was kept in the dark, as you were,
for a very long time.

1070
02:11:16,199 --> 02:11:19,453
- Troubling things.
- Yeah.

1071
02:11:19,620 --> 02:11:23,957
Now we have to sort them out, figure
out who is responsible for what

1072
02:11:24,124 --> 02:11:27,878
and what to do about it.
We have to do this very delicately,

1073
02:11:28,045 --> 02:11:31,965
otherwise people might
get the wrong idea.

1074
02:11:32,132 --> 02:11:34,343
We have to lie.

1075
02:11:35,427 --> 02:11:40,098
- Did I say that?
- No, you didn't.

1076
02:11:40,265 --> 02:11:43,935
- You're upset.
- I'm upset.

1077
02:11:44,102 --> 02:11:49,650
It's understandable. Do you mind
if I give you a bit of advice?

1078
02:11:49,816 --> 02:11:52,110
You know this because you're smart.

1079
02:11:52,277 --> 02:11:56,323
Never make important decisions
while you're upset.

1080
02:11:56,490 --> 02:12:02,037
You did. American soldiers and
civilians are dead because of it.

1081
02:12:02,204 --> 02:12:06,124
- I never ordered any...
- No. Don't play that game with me!

1082
02:12:06,291 --> 02:12:10,462
You won't dishonour their memories
by pretending you didn't know!

1083
02:12:10,629 --> 02:12:14,424
- How dare you lecture...
- How dare you, sir?

1084
02:12:14,591 --> 02:12:18,470
How dare you come here
and bark at me like a junkyard dog!

1085
02:12:18,637 --> 02:12:21,974
I am the President
of the United States!

1086
02:12:25,936 --> 02:12:29,481
It gives me no pleasure
to do it, sir.

1087
02:12:29,648 --> 02:12:32,901
As Acting Deputy Director
of Intelligence it is my duty

1088
02:12:33,068 --> 02:12:37,072
to report this matter
to the Senate Oversight Committee.

1089
02:12:41,994 --> 02:12:44,162
You're not going to do that.

1090
02:12:45,914 --> 02:12:47,874
- I'm not?
- No, no.

1091
02:12:50,127 --> 02:12:54,089
You've got yourself
a chip in the big game now.

1092
02:12:55,382 --> 02:12:57,592
You're going to tuck that away,

1093
02:12:57,759 --> 02:13:01,346
save that for a time
when your own ass is on the line.

1094
02:13:01,513 --> 02:13:04,599
And then you're going to pull it out.

1095
02:13:04,766 --> 02:13:09,229
And I'm going to cash it in for you.
Right?

1096
02:13:11,023 --> 02:13:14,568
I don't think I have anything more
to say to you, sir.

1097
02:13:15,861 --> 02:13:21,325
The country can't afford another
scandal, Jack. To protect itself,

1098
02:13:21,491 --> 02:13:26,997
it won't allow another deception
that goes all the way to the top.

1099
02:13:27,164 --> 02:13:31,043
You'll take the blame. Cutter
and Ritter will take some, too,

1100
02:13:31,209 --> 02:13:34,713
but it won't amount to much,
a slap on the wrist.

1101
02:13:34,880 --> 02:13:40,010
Then $20,000 an hour
on the lecture circuit.

1102
02:13:40,177 --> 02:13:43,972
The rest of the blame
will fall on Greer.

1103
02:13:44,139 --> 02:13:48,101
Yeah, you'll take him down with you.

1104
02:13:48,268 --> 02:13:50,979
You'll destroy his reputation.

1105
02:13:51,146 --> 02:13:56,652
But that's as far as it will go.
The old Potomac two-step, Jack.

1106
02:13:59,488 --> 02:14:03,325
I'm sorry, Mr President,
I don't dance.

1107
02:14:26,348 --> 02:14:28,934
Ryan, have you got a minute?

1108
02:14:29,101 --> 02:14:31,603
No.

1109
02:14:31,770 --> 02:14:34,439
We need to talk!

1110
02:14:34,606 --> 02:14:36,692
Ryan!

1111
02:15:01,008 --> 02:15:06,722
The Committee will come to order.
The Chair will now call Dr Ryan.

1112
02:15:27,659 --> 02:15:31,663
Dr Ryan, thank you for appearing
before the Committee today.

1113
02:15:31,830 --> 02:15:33,540
Thank you, Mr Chairman.

1114
02:15:34,082 --> 02:15:37,544
Please stand
and raise your right hand.

1115
02:15:40,505 --> 02:15:44,468
Do you solemnly swear that
the testimony you're about to give

1116
02:15:44,635 --> 02:15:46,428
is the truth, the whole truth

1117
02:15:46,595 --> 02:15:49,348
and nothing but the truth,
so help you God?

1118
02:15:51,850 --> 02:15:54,019
I do.

1119
02:15:55,604 --> 02:16:00,984
Dr Ryan, you may consider yourself
under oath. Please be seated.

1120
02:16:01,305 --> 02:17:01,910
Watching movies won't make you rich.
Trading can. FilthyRichFutures.com